<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>If you call current() on a Rowset with no rows, or if you call current() when the Rowset iteration key is beyond the count of the Rowset, it throws an error about undefined offset.</p>

<p>The reason is that it's referencing the protected $_data array by the current $_pointer offset, and this may not exist.</p>

<p>Please correct the current() method to return null when requested for an invalid row.  This makes it similar to fetchRow() which returns null if no rows match the conditions.</p>

